cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with object detection and classification in 3D using LiDAR sensors, which is a common task in automated driving. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of a specific algorithm (YOLO v2) and extends its loss function, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with real-time performance, which could place it in cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
